1.What are Conditions in C?
-->Conditions are used to make decisions in a program.
-->Instead of running all code, the program checks something and decides:
** DO this or
**DO that

2.Why we use conditions
-->We use conditions when:
-->You want different outputs based on input
-->You need decision making
-->You want to control program flow
3.Types of conditional statements in C
i. if
    -->Runs code only if condition is true
SYNTAX :
   if (condition) 
     {
              // code
      }
ii. if -else 
    -->choose between between two conditions
SYNTAX :
   if (condition) 
     {
              // code
      }
  else
     {
        //code
     }

iii. if -else if
    -->choose between multiple conditions
SYNTAX :
